qas.question: Features on a browser can range from minimal with little support to what?
When a browser includes a lot of extras, it can be referred to as what?

plausible_answers.text: minimal, text-based user interfaces with bare-bones support for HTML

qas.question: What are some features that IRC has?
What are IRC's sometimes referred to as?

plausible_answers.text: rich user interfaces supporting a wide variety of file formats and protocols

qas.question: What are some features of HTML?
What are some extra features included in IRC?

plausible_answers.text: a wide variety of file formats and protocols
